{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "07", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "11", "M": "40", "S": "48"}}, "news": [{"title": "HMG Stones to invest \u20b940 crore in FY27, eyes \u20b9120-150 crore revenue", "para": "HMG Stones is planning to invest about \u20b940 crore in FY27, including \u20b930 crore in machinery and \u20b910 crore in a new experience centre near Bengaluru airport, as it looks to expand its natural stone business. The company expects revenue to grow to \u20b9120-150 crore in FY27 from over \u20b9100 crore in FY26, even as logistics costs and import dependence remain key concerns.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/hmg-stones-to-invest-40-crore-in-fy27-eyes-120-150-crore-revenue/130888142?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-180122/130888142.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Awfis leases 1.14 lakh sq ft space in Chennai; TEC opens 9,500 sq meters centre in Riyadh", "para": "Awfis Space Solutions has expanded its presence in Chennai by launching two new flexible workspace centres. These additions bring the company's total footprint in the city to 28 centres, covering 8.75 lakh sq ft. Awfis now operates over 200 centres across 18 cities nationwide.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/awfis-expands-presence-in-chennai-with-new-centres-as-tec-launches-facility-in-riyadh/130886807?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96870/130886807.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Bihar cabinet approves decision to raise \u20b94,750-crore World Bank aid for urban development", "para": "Bihar's state cabinet, led by CM Samrat Choudhary, approved raising Rs4,750 crore from the World Bank for urban development projects. The cabinet also sanctioned Rs15,967.03 crore for road maintenance and approved collecting road user fees. Additionally, plans for electric bus procurement and AI training were cleared.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/bihar-cabinet-approves-4750-crore-world-bank-aid-for-urban-development/130878892?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-46628/130878892.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}